    createdAt: 1552595244271,
    descriptionPlain:
      "Vroom.com is a venture-backed, fast-growing start-up focused on revolutionizing the car buying experience. Our approach is unique in that we recondition pre-owned vehicles to a high standard, sell online, and deliver anywhere across the US. We have experienced tremendous growth in our first 5 years of operation and have become a disruptive force in the automotive industry. Vroom is an exciting, accelerating workplace, and there's no better time to join the team than right now.\n\nWe are seeking a bright, experienced, and highly motivated attorney to join our growing legal team as Compliance Counsel. In this role, you will report directly to the Chief Legal Officer and play a key role in supporting Vroom’s compliance with legal and regulatory requirements on both the state and federal level. Our business model is outside of the traditional used car dealership structure, making the ideal candidate someone who can nimbly assess and advise on legal issues using a creative and pragmatic approach. In addition, because we are a small legal team, you will need to be a team player who is flexible and willing to roll up your sleeves and help cover the day-to-day legal needs of the organization. \n",
    description:
      '<div><a href="http://Vroom.com" class="postings-link">Vroom.com</a> is a venture-backed, fast-growing start-up focused on revolutionizing the car buying experience. Our approach is unique in that we recondition pre-owned vehicles to a high standard, sell online, and deliver anywhere across the US. We have experienced tremendous growth in our first 5 years of operation and have become a disruptive force in the automotive industry. Vroom is an exciting, accelerating workplace, and there\'s no better time to join the team than right now.</div><div><br></div><div>We are seeking a bright, experienced, and highly motivated attorney to join our growing legal team as Compliance Counsel. In this role, you will report directly to the Chief Legal Officer and play a key role in supporting Vroom’s compliance with legal and regulatory requirements on both the state and federal level. Our business model is outside of the traditional used car dealership structure, making the ideal candidate someone who can nimbly assess and advise on legal issues using a creative and pragmatic approach. In addition, because we are a small legal team, you will need to be a team player who is flexible and willing to roll up your sleeves and help cover the day-to-day legal needs of the organization.&nbsp;</div>',
